<p class='bodyText' style="margin-top:17px;"><a href="http://www.futureshockstudio.com/" target="new">Future Shock</a> is a professional analog/digital music recording and mixing studio owned by mixer/producer <a href="mailto:newport@alexnewport.com">Alex Newport</a>.</p>
<p class='bodyText' style="margin-top:17px;">Visit the studio's website <a href="http://www.futureshockstudio.com/" target="new">here</a>.</p>
<p class='bodyText'>Located in the uber-hip <a href="http://bushwickbk.com/" target="new">East Williamsburg (AKA Bushwick)</a> area of Brooklyn, the studio includes:
<br /><br />
<ul class="bodyText" style="margin: 0px 55px;">  
	<li style="margin-bottom: 6px;">fully acoustically tuned control room with Tannoy DMT-15 mains and Yamaha NS-10 near fields</li>
	<li style="margin-bottom: 6px;">80 channel Amek Einstein &quot;Super E&quot; analog console with VCA automation, Pro Tools HD, 2&quot; analog, 1/2&quot; and 1/4&quot; analog mixdown, large collection of vintage analog outboard compressors, EQ's and FX.</li>
	<li style="margin-bottom: 6px;">acoustically balanced iso booth with high-quality tie lines to studio</li>
	<li style="margin-bottom: 6px;">extensive microphone and musical equipment selection</li>
	<li>large client lounge with entertainment center, hi speed wi-fi, kitchen,
	  and the all-important Playstation</li>
</ul>
<p class='bodyText'>The studio is located minutes from Manhattan and is easily accessible by car, subway train, and private jet. Street parking is readily available and there's a freight elevator for easy load-in.</p>
<p class='bodyText'>In addition, there are 4 bars within 50 feet of the building, and scores of restaurants/delis/corner stores/cafes/etc within a 2 block radius. McCarren Park and <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kAO4EVMlpwM" target="new">Bedford Avenue</a> are just a few stops away on the L Train.</p>
<p class='bodyText'>affordable accommodation packages are available for bands during sessions.</p>
<p class='bodyText'>Please enquire for details <a href="mailto:newport@alexnewport.com">here</a>.</p>
